  <p>
    The opener was “taste,” which is one of my favorites, and it set the tone right away. The first section kept the energy high with new songs like “Good Graces,” “Slim Pickens,” and “Tornado Warnings.” I felt like I was on cloud nine by the end of that part.
  </p>

  <p>
    The middle set was a full-on jam—fun and dancey—even if those weren’t my absolute top-tier tracks. The final segment brought the big sing-alongs, ending with “Please Please Please,” and then an encore of “Espresso” that had the whole arena bouncing. It was a high-gloss pop show in the best way.
  </p>


</Layout>
